    "body": "Problem:\r\nDeleting another buffer from a float could move focus into the holder window and fire BufEnter for the buffer being deleted.\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\nUse switch_win_noblock() instead of buf_jump_open_win() before recursing into do_buffer_ext().\r\n\r\nFix #39827 \r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39858#discussion_r3258979861"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/39858"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3258979861"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "still must call if `switch_win_noblock` returned fail, but it looks infallible here (maybe assert instead?)\r\nalso could replace the `win_find_tabpage` call by saving its `tp` from the loop?",
            "commit_id": "8bcf6bf847ddf3b312173d8f318b08a343c74a5d",
            "created_at": "2026-05-18T12:45:05Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -1464,10 +1465,33 @@ static int do_buffer_ext(int action, int start, int dir, int count, int flags)\n       close_windows(buf, false);\n       // close_windows keeps the last non-float window. If it still\n       // shows buf, jump there and retry so curbuf gets replaced.\n-      if (bufref_valid(&bufref) && buf->b_nwindows > 0) {\n-        win_T *holder = buf_jump_open_win(buf);\n-        if (holder != NULL && !holder->w_floating) {\n-          return do_buffer_ext(action, start, dir, count, flags);\n+      if (buf != curbuf && bufref_valid(&bufref) && buf->b_nwindows > 0) {\n+        if (curwin->w_floating) {\n+          win_T *holder = NULL;\n+          FOR_ALL_TABS(tp) {\n+            FOR_ALL_WINDOWS_IN_TAB(wp, tp) {\n+              if (wp->w_buffer == buf && !wp->w_floating) {\n+                holder = wp;\n+                break;\n+              }\n+            }\n+            if (holder != NULL) {\n+              break;\n+            }\n+          }\n+          if (holder != NULL) {\n+            switchwin_T switchwin;\n+            if (switch_win_noblock(&switchwin, holder, win_find_tabpage(holder), true) == OK) {\n+              int retval = do_buffer_ext(action, start, dir, count, flags);\n+              restore_win_noblock(&switchwin, true);",
